originalText.text: Margaret made a wonderful presentation called "Achieving A Winning Communication Style."  The audience was a diverse group of women lawyers, investment professionals and others in the asset management industry.  Margaret spoke, in person, about some common communication pitfalls she has encountered over the course of her legal and coaching career and gave ten great tips on building skills and being more at ease with difficult conversations.  Her remarks provided valuable insights and sparked engaging questions and discussion.  It was truly a pleasure to have her as our guest speaker for this event.

originalText.text:
Margaret was a wonderful coach who helped me gain confidence, perspective and direction as I looked for my next career path.  I was a little stuck when we first met but she was engaging, asked good questions, helped me stay focused and challenged me on a number of fronts! I'm happy to say that with Margaret’s help and great/focused coaching and tips, I was able to land a high paying job in a career field that I truly find interesting and that makes me happy!

I would highly recommend Margaret for any of your Career Coaching/Interview/ or Career/Life transition needs. A true professional who can help you get unstuck and unlock your potential!  It is worth taking the time to set up a 1 on 1 appointment with her; she has great insight and truly tries to understand and listen to her clients. Well worth the investment in yourself and your future/goals.

I highly recommend Margaret! 5 Stars!! Book a session with her ASAP!

originalText.text: Margaret is an excellent professional and executive coach.  She is a true coach that both explores opportunities to grow through questions, encouraging you to unpack challenges, feelings and responses, but also offers guidance to help down a path.  Our time has been very influential for me and regardless of where my career takes me, I know it was time extremely well spent.

originalText.text: Margaret is an exceptional coach (and person). She leverages her professional and personal experiences to assist with identifying goals and delineating clear paths to achieving those goals. She is an excellent listener and so clearly passionate about helping others problem solve to achieve their goals. I couldn’t recommend her more!

originalText.text: Margaret is a fantastic career coach. I worked with her when I felt confused about my goals, lacking direction in my career, and overwhelmed by the uncertainty of my future. Through conversation and take-home work, Margaret helped me discern my enjoyable skills, the types of work I would find most fulfilling, and even the lifestyles that would make me happiest. Her personalized and empathetic approach made me feel safe and supported throughout our exploration, and I came away from our work with everything I'd hoped I would. If you're considering a career coach, I recommend Margaret without reservation.
